cit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1704759\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:713:\"<p>On Thursday,Â we released a new version of Eventbrite Tickets that includes a new default post status for imported events. The previous WordPress post statuses available when running Eventbrite imports were Published, Draft, or Pending Review. Going forward,Â Draft,Â Pending Review, and the newÂ (do not override)Â statusesÂ will be available in your Import Settings. Now about theÂ PublishedÂ settingâ€“we&#8217;ll get to that&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/default-import-post-status-eventbrite-events/\">New Default Option for Importing Eventbrite Events</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"George\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11997:\"<p>On Thursday,Â we released a new version of <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-eventbrite-tickets/\">Eventbrite Tickets</a> that includes <strong>a new default post status</strong> for imported events.</p>\n<p>The previous WordPress post statuses available when running Eventbrite imports were <em>Published</em>, <em>Draft</em>, or <em>Pending Review</em>. Going forward,Â <em>Draft</em>,Â <em>Pending Review, </em>and the newÂ <em>(do not override)</em>Â statusesÂ will be available in your Import Settings.</p>\n<p>Now about theÂ <em>PublishedÂ </em>settingâ€“we&#8217;ll get to that in a bit. Trust us, it&#8217;ll make more sense once you&#8217;ve read the info below about the new status.</p>\n<h2>Why Add a New Status?</h2>\n<p>Event organizers often have a mix of <em>Draft</em> and <em>Live</em> events in their account on Eventbrite.com. If your default WordPress import setting isÂ <em>Published</em>,Â that means that all of your<em> Draft</em> events on Eventbrite will be prematurely set to<em> Published</em> on your WordPress site when you run the import.</p>\n<p>For most folks, this is a less than ideal situation. That&#8217;s why we added a new status: <strong><em>(do not override)</em></strong>.</p>\n<h2>The New Default: <em>(do not override)</em></h2>\n<p>In Eventbrite Tickets <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-for-the-week-of-11-february-2019/\">version 4.6.1</a> and higher, the Eventbrite import settings now default to <em>(do not override)</em>, which works very simply: <strong>the Eventbrite.com status is not overridden upon import.</strong></p>\n<p>So if you import a mix of <em>Draft</em> and <em>Live</em> events from Eventbrite.com, the <em>Draft</em> events stay drafts once imported and the <em>Live</em> events are published.</p>\n<h4>Screenshots</h4>\n\n<a href=\'https://theeventscalendar.com/default-import-post-status-eventbrite-events/screen-shot-2019-02-15-at-12-40-32-pm/\'><img width=\"665\" height=\"268\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-665x268.png\" class=\"attachment-large size-large\" alt=\"The (do not override) Status in Settings\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-665x268.png 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-140x56.png 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-300x121.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-768x309.png 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-430x173.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-645x260.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-1068x430.png 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-460x185.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-600x242.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM-500x201.png 500w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.40.32-PM.png 1474w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></a>\n<a href=\'https://theeventscalendar.com/default-import-post-status-eventbrite-events/screen-shot-2019-02-15-at-12-42-56-pm/\'><img width=\"665\" height=\"442\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-665x442.png\" class=\"attachment-large size-large\" alt=\"The (do not override) Status in Imports\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-665x442.png 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-128x85.png 128w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-300x199.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-768x511.png 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-480x320.png 480w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-240x160.png 240w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-720x480.png 720w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-764x508.png 764w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-430x286.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-645x429.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-1068x710.png 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-460x306.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-600x399.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM-500x332.png 500w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2019/02/Screen-Shot-2019-02-15-at-12.42.56-PM.png 1426w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></a>\n\n<h3>FAQs</h3>\n<p><strong>Q:</strong> But what if I <em>want</em> all Eventbrite.com events to be Published on import, even if they&#8217;re drafts on Eventbrite.com?</p>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> We do not recommend doing this, as it could create the problem mentioned above where draft events are published prematurely. However, one can force all Eventbrite imports to be <em>Published</em> on import by adding the following code snippet to your site:</p>\n<pre>function force_eb_events_to_always_import_as_published( $post_status, $event, $record  ) {\n\n    if ( ! isset( $event[\'eventbrite\']-&gt;status ) ) {\n        return $post_status;\n    }\n\n    return \'publish\';\n}\n\nadd_filter( \'tribe_aggregator_new_event_post_status_before_import\', \'force_eb_events_to_always_import_as_published\', 20, 3 );\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Q:</strong> Why are the &#8220;Use global import settings&#8221; and &#8220;Published&#8221; options removed from the WordPress import settings for Eventbrite?</p>\n<p><strong>A:</strong> Both the &#8220;Use global import settings&#8221; and &#8220;Published&#8221; options could lead to the issue mentioned above where draft Eventbrite.com events are imported and prematurely published. To help make sure this doesn&#8217;t happen, we&#8217;ve removed both options from settings screen for Eventbrite imports.</p>\n<p>If you have any other questions, comments, or concerns about this new feature, swing by our <a href=\"https://support.theeventscalendar.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Help Desk</a> and let us know!</p>\n<p><em>For more of the latest news from The Events Calendar, sign up for our monthly newsletter.</em></p>\n\n                <div class=\'gf_browser_unknown gform_wrapper gutenberg-email-form_wrapper\' id=\'gform_wrapper_31\' ><form method=\'post\' enctype=\'multipart/form-data\'  id=\'gform_31\' class=\'gutenberg-email-form\' action=\'/feed/\'>\n                        <div class=\'gform_body\'><ul id=\'gform_fields_31\' class=\'gform_fields top_label form_sublabel_below description_below\'><li id=\'field_31_7\'  class=\'gfield field_sublabel_above field_description_above gfield_visibility_visible\' ><label class=\'gfield_label gfield_label_before_complex\' for=\'input_31_7_3\' >Name</label><div class=\'ginput_complex ginput_container no_prefix has_first_name no_middle_name has_last_name no_suffix gf_name_has_2 ginput_container_name gfield_trigger_change\' id=\'input_31_7\'>\n                            \n                            <span id=\'input_31_7_3_container\' class=\'name_first\' >\n                                                    <label for=\'input_31_7_3\' >First</label>\n                                                    <input type=\'text\' name=\'input_7.3\' id=\'input_31_7_3\' value=\'\' aria-label=\'First 